===Features===
*"Com-Scan Extra: [[The Art of Howard Chaykin]]"
*:<small>When he came across some old ''Star Wars'' illustrations Pete Vilmur turned detective to discover their origins. Little did he think he'd uncovered some lost [[Howard Chaykin]] art!</small>
*"[[Mark Hamill & Carrie Fisher: Luke & Leia]]" {{C|by [[Brian J. Robb]], [[Jonathan Wilkins]], & [[Brigid Cherry]]}}
*:<small>Rarely interviewed about his ''Star Wars'' experiences, Mark Hamill sits down one-on-one with ''Star Wars Insider'' to discuss his Force-filled memories. As a bonus, we also present some selected highlights from actress Carrie Fisher's appearance at ''Star Wars'': Celebration IV.</small>
*"[["You're Hired" to be Darth Vader's Secret Apprentice!]]"{{C|by Brian J. Robb & Jonathan Wilkins}}
*:<small>''Star Wars Insider'' meets LucasArts Project Lead Haden Blackman and "Secret Apprentice" actor [[Sam Witwer]] to get the lowdown on the next chapter of the ''Star Wars Saga: ''The Force Unleashed''</small>
*"[[Pirates of the Boards]]: Part V" {{C|by [[Jonathan W. Rinzler]]}}
*:<small>Mixing and matching Gold, Red, and Blue Leaders&mdash;the trench runs on the Death Star exhaust port begin! Explore [[Joe Johnston]]'s early ''Star Wars'' storyboards.</small>
*"[[Art Vader]]" {{C|by [[Bonnie Burton]]}}
*:<small>This is Darth Vader as you've never seen him before! We check out The Vader Project.</small>

==Continuity==
According to [http://www.tfaw.com TFAW.com], ''Insider'' #97 was originally scheduled to be the "Special Effects" issue; however, that issue was most likely postponed until [[Star Wars Insider 98|#98]].<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.tfaw.com/Profile/Star-Wars-Insider-97-%28Newsstand-Edition%29___285151|text=TFAW.com - Star Wars Insider #97 (Newsstand Edition)|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/HOTW1|nolive=1}}</ref>

While issue #97 was released in October of 2007, it is listed as the December issue on both the cover and page 7.

